  What is Dependency Injection (DI) ?

Dependency Injection (DI) is a design pattern where the Spring container creates objects and injects their dependencies automatically instead of us creating them using the new keyword.

Without DI, classes become tightly coupled because they directly create their dependent objects. With DI, the application becomes loosely coupled, easier to test, and more maintainable.

Spring Boot uses Inversion of Control (IoC) through the ApplicationContext container.
When the application starts, Spring scans classes using component scanning, creates beans for classes annotated with @RestController, @Service, @Repository, and @Component, and stores them in the container.

Then it injects required dependencies automatically using constructor injection or @Autowired.


